benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Add custom fields to account

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC13, @TC14, @TC16, @TC20, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC29, @TC30 cover successful creation with valid data and headers.

Invalid Payload: @TC06 (invalid accountId), @TC08 (malformed JSON), @TC09 (empty body), @TC10 (non-existent account), @TC11 (unsupported fields), @TC12 (duplicate fields), @TC16 (unauthorized), @TC18 (SQL injection), @TC19 (XSS), @TC28 (invalid data types), @TC30 (null values) cover various invalid input scenarios.
Edge Cases: @TC26 (empty array), @TC27 (partial input), @TC28 (unexpected data types), @TC29 (max/min values) cover boundary and edge cases.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC23, @TC24 ensure previous bugs and backward compatibility are tested.
Performance & Load: @TC21, @TC22 test response times and concurrent requests.
Security: @TC18, @TC19 test injection and XSS vulnerabilities.
gaps: Authorization: No explicit tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens beyond @TC16.
Rate Limiting: No tests for handling multiple requests in rapid succession.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Pagination: No tests for handling large datasets with pagination.
Service Unavailability: No tests simulating dependent service failures or downtime.
Retry Logic: No tests for transient network failures and retries (@TC20 partially covers this).
Response Content Validation: Limited checks on response body structure beyond matching created fields.
Timeouts: No tests for request timeouts or server delays.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for authorization failures, such as missing or invalid tokens.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system handles high request volumes gracefully.
Include scenarios for caching headers to ensure proper cache invalidation and validation.
Create tests for pagination when dealing with large numbers of custom fields.
Simulate dependent service failures to verify system resilience and error handling.
Develop tests for retry mechanisms on transient network issues.
Enhance response validation to check for correct error messages and response formats.
Test request timeouts and server delays to ensure system stability under slow network conditions.
